  "commentary": "**Dealer Hedging Commentary:**\n\nDealers are actively buying the dip as SPX sits between the massive negative gamma wall at 6570 (-34.7B) and positive gamma at 6600 (+47.4B), with the recent GEX surge indicating heavy options flow that's forcing systematic hedging activity. The PIN regime structure creates a tight 30-point range where dealers will aggressively buy any move toward 6570 and sell strength into 6600, making this a classic mean-reversion setup with heavy two-way flow. Watch for violent snapbacks if we break below 6570 (dealer buying accelerates) or grind higher into 6600 where dealer selling should cap the move.",
